  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA213-kiḷavi">itu matiyuṭampaṭukkun talaimakaṉ colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is what HE said who is bringing [their] minds into agreement.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA213">
<l>            aruvi yārkkum peruvarai naṇṇik</l>
<l>            kaṉṟukāl yātta maṉṟap palaviṉ</l>
<l>            vērkkoṇṭu tūṅkuṅ koḻuñcuḷaip perumpaḻaṅ</l>
<l>            kuḻavic cētā mānti yayalatu</l>
<l>            vēypayi liṟumpi ṉāmūṟal parukum </l>
<l>            peruṅkal vēlic ciṟukuṭi yāteṉac</l>
<l>            collavuñ collī rāyiṟ kalleṉak</l>
<l>            karuvi māmaḻai vīḻnteṉa veḻunta</l>
<l>            ceṅkē ḻāṭiya ceḻuṅkuraṟ ciṟutiṉaik</l>
<l>            koypuṉaṅ kāvalu numatō </l>
<l>kōṭēn talku ṉīṭō ḷīrē. maiyeḻi luṇkaṇ maṭanal līrē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent">*Which is [your] small hamlet with a fence of big stones,</l>
<l rend="indent">lying in the great mountains where the waterfall roars,</l>
<l rend="indent2">where the red cow with calf feeds on the big fruit</l>
<l rend="indent3">with rich pulp that hangs down to the root of the jack-tree</l>
<l rend="indent3">on the village common, where the calf is bound by [its] leg,</l>
<l rend="indent2">[and] drinks from the flow of water in a rustling bamboo thicket nearby?*</l>
<l rend="indent">If you don’t speak, even if spoken to [thus]</l>
<l rend="indent">– is the watch of the field your’s too, where they pluck</l>
<l rend="indent">the small millet with abundant ears on which red lustre played<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">ceṅ kēḻ āṭiya</term>: what does this attribute signify?</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent">that had risen since rain had descended in great amount, noisily,</l>
<l rend="indent2">o you of long shoulder [and] hips with eminent curves?</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
